N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 16.105 - Duration, expiration and termination of specific licenses

State Regulations
(a) Except as otherwise provided in this subdivision, each specific license will expire at the end of the expiration date stated in such license. If any licensee duly files with the department not less than 30 days prior to such expiration date, an application in accordance with section
16.102
of this Part for the renewal of his license or for a new and superseding license, such license shall not be deemed to have expired until the department has finally determined such application. (b) The department may terminate any specific license upon the written request of the licensee. Notes
